expanded="true"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1274</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:addr>erct-0041</fr:addr><fr:route>erct-0041.xml</fr:route><fr:title>The <fr:link
href="erct-000W.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000W">coherent remainder</fr:link> of a <fr:link
href="erct-000Y.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000Y">section</fr:link></fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>18</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:meta
name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link
href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0041.agda"
type="external">erct-0041.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Given a function <fr:tex>f \colon  A \to  B</fr:tex> and a <fr:link
href="erct-000Y.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000Y">section</fr:link> <fr:tex>g \colon  B \to  A</fr:tex> witnessed by <fr:tex>\epsilon \colon  f \circ  g =  1_{ B }</fr:tex>, we define the <fr:em><fr:strong>coherent remainder</fr:strong></fr:em> of <fr:tex>\mathopen {} \left ( g, \epsilon \right ) \mathclose {}</fr:tex> to be the following sum:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block">   \mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{ f } \mathopen {} \left ( g, \epsilon \right ) \mathclose {}  : \equiv   \mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \eta : g \circ  f  \sim   1_{ A } \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \eta : g \circ  f  \sim   1_{ A } \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \eta : g \circ  f  \sim   1_{ A } \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \eta : g \circ  f  \sim   1_{ A } \right ) \mathclose {} } }    \mathsf {act}_{ f } \circ   \eta   \sim   \epsilon   \circ  f </fr:tex><fr:p>For any <fr:tex>f \colon  A \to  B</fr:tex>, it is evident that the type of <fr:link
href="erct-000W.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000W">inverses</fr:link> to <fr:tex>f</fr:tex> is (up to reassociation) precisely the dependent sum <fr:tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \mathsf {section} \, f \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \mathsf {section} \, f \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \mathsf {section} \, f \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \mathsf {section} \, f \right ) \mathclose {} } } \mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{ f }</fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1276</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:addr>erct-0042</fr:addr><fr:route>erct-0042.xml</fr:route><fr:title><fr:link
href="erct-0041.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0041">Coherent remainder</fr:link> as a <fr:link
href="erct-0010.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0010">path object</fr:link></fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>18</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:meta
name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link
href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0042.agda"
type="external">erct-0042.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex>f \colon  A \to  B</fr:tex> be a function equipped with a <fr:link
href="erct-000Y.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000Y">section</fr:link> <fr:tex>\sigma   \equiv   \mathopen {} \left ( g \colon  B \to  A, \epsilon \colon  f \circ  g =  1_{ B } \right ) \mathclose {}</fr:tex>. We can equip the <fr:link
href="erct-0041.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0041">coherent remainder</fr:link> of <fr:tex>\sigma</fr:tex> with the structure of a <fr:link
href="erct-0010.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0010">path object</fr:link> as follows:</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li>
  We equip <fr:tex>g \circ  f \sim   1_{ A }</fr:tex> with the following <fr:link
href="erct-001C.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001C">dependent product</fr:link> of <fr:link
href="erct-0013.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0013">intrinsic path object</fr:link> structures:
  <fr:tex
display="block">     \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }      \mathord { \vartriangle }       \mathopen {} \left (       g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {}  = x      \right ) \mathclose {}         </fr:tex></fr:li>
 <fr:li>
  For each <fr:tex>\eta \colon  g \circ  f \sim 1_{ A }</fr:tex>, we likewise equip <fr:tex>\mathsf {act}_{ f } \circ \eta \sim   \epsilon \circ  f</fr:tex> with the following <fr:link
href="erct-001C.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001C">dependent product</fr:link> of <fr:link
href="erct-0013.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0013">intrinsic path object</fr:link> structures:
  <fr:tex
display="block">     \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }      \mathord { \vartriangle }       \mathopen {} \left (        \mathsf {act}_{ f } \mathopen {} \left ( \eta  x \right ) \mathclose {}  =  \epsilon \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {}       \right ) \mathclose {}         </fr:tex></fr:li>
 <fr:li><fr:p>We exhibit the latter as a <fr:link
href="erct-0032.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0032">right-cloven family of path objects</fr:link> over the former with the cleaving that for <fr:tex>\eta _0, \eta _1 \colon  g \circ  f \sim   1_{ A }</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>\eta _{01} \colon   \eta _0  \sim   \eta _1</fr:tex> defines <fr:tex>\eta _{01}^* \colon   \mathsf {act}_{ f } \circ \eta _1 \sim   \epsilon \circ  f  \to   \mathsf {act}_{ f } \circ   \eta _0 \sim \epsilon \circ  f</fr:tex> as follows:</fr:p>
  <fr:tex
display="block">     \begin {aligned}     &amp; \eta _{01}^* \chi  : \equiv       \lambda x \mathpunct {.}       \mathsf {act}_{ \mathsf {act}_{ f } } \mathopen {} \left ( \eta _{01}x \right ) \mathclose {} \cdot   \chi  x     \end {aligned}   </fr:tex></fr:li></fr:ol><fr:p>With this cleaving in mind, finally define <fr:tex>\mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{ f } \sigma</fr:tex> to be the following <fr:link
href="erct-0036.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0036">contravariant sum</fr:link> of <fr:link
href="erct-0010.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0010">path objects</fr:link>:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block">   \mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{ f } \sigma  : \equiv    \mathchoice { \textstyle \int _{ \mathopen {} \left (     \eta :    \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }     \mathord { \vartriangle }      \mathopen {} \left ( g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {} =x \right ) \mathclose {}        \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \int _{ \mathopen {} \left (     \eta :    \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }     \mathord { \vartriangle }      \mathopen {} \left ( g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {} =x \right ) \mathclose {}        \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \int _{ \mathopen {} \left (     \eta :    \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }     \mathord { \vartriangle }      \mathopen {} \left ( g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {} =x \right ) \mathclose {}        \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \int _{ \mathopen {} \left (     \eta :    \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }     \mathord { \vartriangle }      \mathopen {} \left ( g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {} =x \right ) \mathclose {}        \right ) \mathclose {} } }    \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }    \mathord { \vartriangle }     \mathopen {} \left (      \mathsf {act}_{ f } \mathopen {} \left ( \eta  x \right ) \mathclose {}  =  \epsilon \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {}     \right ) \mathclose {}     </fr:tex><fr:p>Given elements <fr:tex>\mathopen {} \left ( \eta _0, \chi _0 \right ) \mathclose {}</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>\mathopen {} \left ( \eta _1, \chi _1 \right ) \mathclose {}</fr:tex> of <fr:tex>\mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{ f } \sigma</fr:tex>, the resulting type <fr:tex>\mathopen {} \left ( \eta _0, \chi _0 \right ) \mathclose {} \cong _{ \mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{ f } \sigma } \mathopen {} \left ( \eta _1, \chi _1 \right ) \mathclose {}</fr:tex> is definitionally equivalent to the following dependent sum:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block">   \mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \eta _{01}: \eta _0 \sim   \eta _1 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \eta _{01}: \eta _0 \sim   \eta _1 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \eta _{01}: \eta _0 \sim   \eta _1 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \eta _{01}: \eta _0 \sim   \eta _1 \right ) \mathclose {} } }    \chi _0  \sim   \lambda x \mathpunct {.}   \mathsf {act}_{ \mathsf {act}_{ f } } \mathopen {} \left ( \eta _{01}x \right ) \mathclose {} \cdot   \chi _1 x </fr:tex></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
