 <fr:p>Without loss of generality, we may assume that <fr:tex>f</fr:tex> has an <fr:link
href="erct-000W.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000W">inverse</fr:link> <fr:tex>\mathopen {} \left ( g, \epsilon , \eta , \chi \right ) \mathclose {}</fr:tex>. By <fr:ref
addr="erct-0026"
href="erct-0026.xml"
taxon="Lemma"></fr:ref>, it suffices to argue that the type of <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">inverses</fr:link> to <fr:tex>f</fr:tex> is a <fr:link
href="erct-0025.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0025">retract</fr:link> of a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">proposition</fr:link>; the type of <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">inverses</fr:link> to <fr:tex>f</fr:tex> is in fact equivalent to the type of <fr:link
href="erct-000Y.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000Y">sections</fr:link> equipped with a <fr:link
href="erct-0041.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0041">coherent remainder</fr:link>:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex
display="block">    \mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \sigma : \mathsf {section} \, f \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \sigma : \mathsf {section} \, f \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \sigma : \mathsf {section} \, f \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \sigma : \mathsf {section} \, f \right ) \mathclose {} } }     \mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{ f } \sigma   </fr:tex>

 <fr:p>By <fr:ref
addr="erct-001M"
href="erct-001M.xml"
taxon="Lemma"></fr:ref>, it suffices to show that the type of <fr:link
href="erct-000Y.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000Y">sections</fr:link> to <fr:tex>f</fr:tex> is a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">proposition</fr:link> and that for every such <fr:link
href="erct-000Y.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000Y">section</fr:link>, the <fr:link
href="erct-0041.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0041">coherent remainder</fr:link> thereof is a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">proposition</fr:link>. The latter is <fr:ref
addr="erct-0043"
href="erct-0043.xml"
taxon="Lemma"></fr:ref>, and the former follows from <fr:ref
addr="erct-002Q"
href="erct-002Q.xml"
taxon="Lemma"></fr:ref> by means of the <fr:link
href="erct-000Y.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000Y">retraction</fr:link> <fr:tex>\mathopen {} \left ( g, \eta \right ) \mathclose {}</fr:tex>.</fr:p>
